content.description: Climb a slab to a short roof with good holds.  A big move to a huge jug is required to move past the roof.  A few more moves brings you to the anchors.
content.protection: Six bolts to fixed steel cleaning biners. Please DO NOT use the fixed biners for toptoping
content.location: This is the left hand route.

content.description: Big holds on pretty bomber stone.  Slab to a ledge then pull a slight belly before tackling the upper headwall. Climbs right of the bolt line.
content.protection: Five bolts to fixed steel cleaning biners. Please DO NOT use the fixed biners for toproping. üëç
content.location: This is the right hand line.

content.description: Located alongside of the road leading down into the park Primal Wall hosts two routes on very nice stone. Please be mindful of vehicle traffic on the road while at this wall. If you are spectating please keep off the road.
